TextBlock.TextLine: London m Abram Vivian
Antwerp 30 gber 1682
y mij last to you was on the 26 courant sence recd. y of 11 & 15 ditto where by
finde that you mustake my lesters, or do not under stand mee s alwayes
told you & so do shill, that never you must send any bayes or kerseis by wad
of rotterdam, bust cloth, because the charges uppon cloathes by that way of
are inconsiderable, where as bayes & carsies will not bare itt, so if you
examin my lest letters iyou will finde, that es alwayes exspressed cloathe
to be sent by rotterdam which pray observe for the future, and lett a bale
of dosins and one of northrens more bye sent that way of any op ortunitn
presents sooner then pindar. I have woor you the 16t o have the bayes
sent up to london, because formmerly . had goods so, which then were
re shipped there: butt seeng the heary bayes are sent by way of rosterdam
lett the kersies come by pindar, by which I exspert the rest of al my
orders compleated, & lett yd freinds do the best they con, for wee may n
tye them tog a pennie though I could nisth to have dosins att 3„5 a 6„
yett lest him dohis best, give hun fal order to do as for him self, that
so he may finde no reason to complaine, or to be backward, for the sime
of sale is non & wish in 2 months is past, or aft for thest till ½ aber
& had I goods I could gelt mony non, the 4 bacles arrived by smith are
non aff the key here, batt that suply doubt will not serve my turne
for 8 dayes : so pray proceed wisely, & make no mistakes I have given you
creditt too the bale N78, if these reds be prest all the clooth over itt
will be well enough, butt as I told you before the lost when not nrest
att al, I doubt you have from mee, because I finde the reds bought
which last I ordered, & what fiest ordened & finde not as yett
tought I exspects that all shall be punctually compleated by pindar
I shall accept yd bull & pass to yd acctt & by nont post shall advise
you how to do, to warde payment of the goods a buynge inclosed you have
a note of 2 banes and sonce frances deliverede board akings gaght the
2 banck y. 21 pictures 10 more are in N1 aboard p de wolf a binlander
each hath some fronces 14 in all the rest shall follow p first not beeng
ready: p nent invoyce & se wonder heare nothing of the lacetradt
from you, ofhers are vere brish ast ytt m on moons inquires som
times if I have no orders to buy more & how they sell: pray a word remaine
London John Loyd
30 sber i62
according to what I wrott to you on the 26 cuust have shipped aboor
aboard peeter de wolg a pack of tykes, ascording to the inclosed note in
the £ 3 seales marked nith a line undor the contingh beeng in 3 ps are
N11 p of laces, besides & have sent you & p of lace connrade up ni a
small packettKN1 bj a kings yaght which also not went away y
yeasterday, the doefor heefor soone hath ytt as by the inclosed note you
will see, god sending al safe to yd hand, I and sure you will make ift word
yd will, because itt is bought vere well & godd cheap, for the cost, & charges
pleasets give mue credit, whilst nith lende saluts I' remaine
of the laces are in the tykes
with the yaght
the & 2 seales are 2 in one & noted
2 seales the 3 great lead also
& maghed great lead
london Henry Collier
ntwerp 30 gber 162
& my last to you was on the 26t cintt sence non from you, inclosed
a note of the bale of tykes & N 26 shipped for you aboard of p de wolf
which went from heme yeasterday, itt is assorted nith seu of all the sorts,
& hope will geve content, which, is the need full att prosont from
Brussel Steven Kints
C 30 d.
In antw. aenn den ul van gistren de baijen n hebben maer heden connen gelest woorden
soo dat ick de selve morgen aen ul & beurtschip tot seynde, als mede de fijne geperste
mod. spaens laecken, waer van de facture as dan sal volgen, hope ul alles schrdrgh
sal in rujs hebben, & soo wanneer ijts anders soo ul dinsl voor valt
ten is mijne fauten niet dat de goederen soo lanck tardeeren, alsoo die nu van ostende onderegen
sijn geweest
